Created by PLY version 3.11 (http://www.dabeaz.com/ply)

Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statements
Rule 2     statements -> statement statements
Rule 3     statements -> statement
Rule 4     statement -> declaration
Rule 5     statement -> assignment
Rule 6     statement -> print_statement
Rule 7     statement -> repeat_statement
Rule 8     statement -> cycle_statement
Rule 9     statement -> check_statement
Rule 10    declaration -> NUM IDENTIFIER ASSIGN expression
Rule 11    assignment -> IDENTIFIER ASSIGN expression
Rule 12    print_statement -> SHOW IDENTIFIER
Rule 13    repeat_statement -> WHILE LPAREN condition RPAREN LBRACE statements RBRACE
Rule 14    cycle_statement -> FOR LPAREN assignment SEMICOLON condition SEMICOLON assignment RPAREN LBRACE statements RBRACE
Rule 15    check_statement -> IF LPAREN condition RPAREN LBRACE statements RBRACE else_clause
Rule 16    else_clause -> ELSE LBRACE statements RBRACE
Rule 17    else_clause -> ELIF LPAREN condition RPAREN LBRACE statements RBRACE else_clause
Rule 18    else_clause -> <empty>
Rule 19    condition -> expression LT expression
Rule 20    condition -> expression GT expression
Rule 21    condition -> expression LE expression
Rule 22    condition -> expression GE expression
Rule 23    condition -> expression EQ expression
Rule 24    condition -> expression NE expression
Rule 25    expression -> expression PLUS term
Rule 26    expression -> expression MINUS term
Rule 27    expression -> term
Rule 28    term -> term MULTIPLY factor
Rule 29    term -> term DIVIDE factor
Rule 30    term -> factor
Rule 31    factor -> NUMBER
Rule 32    factor -> IDENTIFIER
Rule 33    factor -> LPAREN expression RPAREN

Terminals, with rules where they appear

ASSIGN               : 10 11
DIVIDE               : 29
ELIF                 : 17
ELSE                 : 16
EQ                   : 23
FOR                  : 14
GE                   : 22
GT                   : 20
IDENTIFIER           : 10 11 12 32
IF                   : 15
LBRACE               : 13 14 15 16 17
LE                   : 21
LPAREN               : 13 14 15 17 33
LT                   : 19
MINUS                : 26
MULTIPLY             : 28
NE                   : 24
NUM                  : 10
NUMBER               : 31
PLUS                 : 25
RBRACE               : 13 14 15 16 17
RPAREN               : 13 14 15 17 33
SEMICOLON            : 14 14
SHOW                 : 12
WHILE                : 13
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

assignment           : 5 14 14
check_statement      : 9
condition            : 13 14 15 17
cycle_statement      : 8
declaration          : 4
else_clause          : 15 17
expression           : 10 11 19 19 20 20 21 21 22 22 23 23 24 24 25 26 33
factor               : 28 29 30
print_statement      : 6
program              : 0
repeat_statement     : 7
statement            : 2 3
statements           : 1 2 13 14 15 16 17
term                 : 25 26 27 28 29

